                <p>For many small business owners in the Netherlands, the end of the month triggers a familiar, time-consuming ritual: the invoicing marathon. It's a multi-stage race against the clock involving creating invoices, chasing down project details, manually calculating BTW (VAT), emailing PDFs, and then, the most frustrating part—chasing late payments. On the other side of the coin is the mountain of supplier invoices that pile up, demanding manual data entry, approvals, and processing.</p>

